JOHANNESBURG - The Constitutional Court is set to consider whether new property owners should be held responsible for the previous owner's municipal debt.In November, the North Gauteng High Court ruled the practice unconstitutional.WATCH: Municipalities need to collect more money - ZumaThe cities of Tshwane and Ekurhuleni then indicated that they would appeal the decision.The High Court ruling was referred to the Constitutional Court for confirmation.A full bench of the court is expected to hear the confirmation and appeal applications on Tuesday.eNCA